reviewText:
Pros:
+only farming simulator worth buying;
+adition of forestry;
+7 types of corps;
+lots of vehicles.

Cons:
-poor vehicle grip (feels like driving on ice sometimes);
-you will get bored by sound of vehicles;
-few updates with bug repairs;
-game gets boring after a while.

Final word: I would recommend this game only if you like farming or forestry and if you do not mind poor physics. Music you like is recomended becaose you will want to mute the game after hour of driving.

PROS:
+ Great atmosphere in the maps;
+ Licensed products; (No Nan/Old Nolland);
+ You can choose what parking style you want;

CONS:
– AI is way to slow;
– £/$/€12,000 starting on easy is too low;
– Similarities to Farming Simulator 2013 are quite obvious;
– Two maps (PLEASE GIANTS MAKE MORE NEXT TIME!);
– Sync and lots of LAG in Multiplayer;
– Same boring AI;
– Lack of detail on roads;
– £20 is too high for a game with that low of a graphics engine;
– DLC's add to little for the price;

Conclusion:
I love the game. Hours of fun. I know almost all the names, places etc. The graphics could be a lot better and sync in Multiplayer is a let down. Three out of Five Stars!

